have responded to this as above.
  3.  Superficial cleaning, fogging, or painting over residues cannot ensur=
e long-term safety or durability.
  4.  Bricks and mortar are porous: once penetrated by smoke and chemical r=
esidues, they can continue to off-gas and deteriorate over time, underminin=
g both habitability and structural performance.
  5.
  6.  Similarly, timber framing, structural timbers, and plasterboard linin=
gs are fibrous and absorbent. Once smoke and chemical residues penetrate, t=
hey may release odours, compromise air quality, accelerate corrosion of emb=
edded fixings, and create conditions for hidden mould or decay. These risks=
 cannot be fully eliminated by surface cleaning
  7.  Your approach appears to focus only on visible damage (e.g. darkened =
beams), while overlooking non-visible but equally serious fire, smoke, and =
