<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:1.0pt;color:white">Hi Grant=
, I am following up on our visit to the property on Tuesday. I left the mee=
ting feeling quite confused about several points, and I would be grateful i=
f you could please clarify the following
 so I can properly understand the approach</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">Hi Grant,<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">I am following up on our visit to the property on Tuesday. I left the =
meeting feeling quite confused about several points, and I would be gratefu=
l if you could please clarify the following
 so I can properly understand the approach Tower is taking:<o:p></o:p></spa=
n></p>
<p><b><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans=
-serif">1. Independent expert testing</span></b><span style=3D"font-size:9.=
0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-serif"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">You indicated that Tower/you will not pay for any expert testing as pa=
rt of my preparation of the claim, as you said that is what you are already=
 doing. However, I am struggling to understand
 this position. From my perspective, you are preparing the claim from Tower=
=E2=80=99s side, and I have not been invited to or involved in any of the N=
ZRSC<span class=3D"apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"color=
:#0070C0">[can you please clarify what NZRSC stands
 for? =E2=80=93 I am sorry, I am not familiar with this acronym]<span class=
=3D"apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span>assessments or discussions. =
This does not feel independent or transparent from my side.<span class=3D"a=
pple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"color:#0070C0">Attached
 are the material damage Report &amp; Scope of repair works as provided by =
our technical Building consultant. These are provided to you for your refer=
ence and review. I received these from ASURNZ o Friday 5<sup>th</sup><span =
class=3D"apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>September.
 &nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">Given the seriousness of the fire, and the chemical involvement (inclu=
ding spa chemicals with corrosive chlorides and bromides), I am concerned t=
hat critical risks may be under-assessed. Could
 you please clarify why Tower would not support me in engaging independent =
engineers, hygienists, or other specialists to provide an impartial view?<s=
pan class=3D"apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"color:#0070=
C0">We can provide independent swab-testing
 by a forensic scientist, which tests for chemical contamination which has =
occurred from the fire. I would need to meet with you to have you provide c=
ontext and detail on exactly what chemicals were present and where they wer=
e located within the property. I
 am happy to progress this process further with you as soon as possible =E2=
=80=93 but I will need to establish more context and detail as to what this=
 potential contamination may be, before we undertake any testing. We can al=
so share the methodology of the forensic
 testing with you before we undertake the testing. &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><o:p>=
</o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">Further, I request that I be&nbsp;included in all communications with =
any assessors&nbsp;and 3rd parties=E2=80=94 including texts, emails, calls,=
 and meetings =E2=80=94 and that these be scheduled so I have the opportuni=
ty
 to participate. This is essential for transparency and to ensure I am prop=
erly informed about the basis of decisions being made.<span class=3D"apple-=
converted-space">&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"color:#0070C0">I can accommoda=
te this as much as is practically possible.
 I have kept you fully informed of every step and process that I have under=
taken to date when progressing your claim. I understand that you have made =
a privacy request to our claims department =E2=80=93 which will provide you=
 with access to all communications regarding
 your claim. I will forward this request that you have made to a<span class=
=3D"apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><u>Senior Claims Manager</u><span c=
lass=3D"apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>=E2=80=93 so that they can resp=
ond to your request in a more comprehensive response.
 This is a Claims Management request =E2=80=93 whereas my focus is on the s=
tructural repairs required for your claim. Please allow to forward and esca=
late this request for you. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><b><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans=
-serif">2. Structural elements =E2=80=93 linings and framing</span></b><spa=
n style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-serif"><o=
:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">You mentioned that, in addition to demolishing and rebuilding the clos=
ed deck, your intention is to replace only a couple of structural beams and=
 to rely on methods such as dry-ice blasting
 and thermal fogging for the bricks. From a technical perspective, this see=
ms inadequate because:<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<div>
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"1" type=3D"1">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l5 level1 lfo6">Smoke odour and r=
esidue remain even on the first floor =E2=80=94 the least affected part of =
the house =E2=80=94 three months after the fire, suggesting deep penetratio=
n.<span class=3D"apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></li><li cl=
ass=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l5 level1 lfo6">The fire involved spa c=
hemicals, creating corrosive residues (chlorides, bromides) likely absorbed=
 into linings, timber framing, and fixings.<span class=3D"apple-converted-s=
pace">&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"color:#0070C0">I
 have responded to this as above.</span><o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNor=
mal" style=3D"mso-list:l5 level1 lfo6">Superficial cleaning, fogging, or pa=
inting over residues cannot ensure long-term safety or durability.<o:p></o:=
p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l5 level1 lfo6">Bricks and=
 mortar are porous: once penetrated by smoke and chemical residues, they ca=
n continue to off-gas and deteriorate over time, undermining both habitabil=
ity and structural performance.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" styl=
e=3D"mso-list:l5 level1 lfo6">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal"=
 style=3D"mso-list:l5 level1 lfo6">Similarly, timber framing, structural ti=
mbers, and plasterboard linings are fibrous and absorbent. Once smoke and c=
hemical residues penetrate, they may release odours, compromise air quality=
, accelerate
 corrosion of embedded fixings, and create conditions for hidden mould or d=
ecay. These risks cannot be fully eliminated by surface cleaning<o:p></o:p>=
</li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l5 level1 lfo6">Your approac=
h appears to focus only on visible damage (e.g. darkened beams), while over=
looking non-visible but equally serious fire, smoke, and water impacts. Thi=
s is not appropriate, creates significant
 long-term risks, and is not aligned with Tower=E2=80=99s obligation to rei=
nstate the house to an =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D standard.<o:p></o:p></li></=
ol>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">On that basis, could you clarify how retaining conta=
minated bricks, timbers, and linings meets Tower=E2=80=99s obligation to re=
instate the property to a =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D standard? What testing a=
nd certification is planned to ensure these critical services
 are restored to a safe and =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D condition?<o:p></o:p><=
/p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><b>3. Roof assessment</b><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">You indicated that the roof requires no work. I find this difficult to=
 reconcile with the evidence<span style=3D"color:#0070C0">: [ with respect =
I said that there was no structural fire damage
 in the roof space. It could be accepted that there is a faint smoke odour =
in the roof space from any smoke which may have passed through this space. =
We have allowed for replacement of 95 sqm of ceiling insulation to eliminat=
e the possibility of any smoke odours
 remaining.</span><span class=3D"apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;=
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"1" type=3D"1">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l1 level1 lfo7">Large volumes of =
black smoke were seen coming out from all sides of the roof during the fire=
.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l1 level1 lfo7">=
A gutter was significantly heat-damaged.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNor=
mal" style=3D"color:#0070C0;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo7"><span style=3D"color:w=
indowtext">Local reporting even suggested the fire appeared to be in the ro=
of. I have been in the roof space.<span class=3D"apple-converted-space">&nb=
sp;</span></span>There is
 no structural fire damage in the roof space.<span class=3D"apple-converted=
-space">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></li></ol>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">If external heat was sufficient to damage guttering, then internal ele=
ments such as roof cavity insulation, underlay, battens, fixings, and truss=
es may also have been affected. Could you please
 clarify what inspection methods were used to conclude the roof was undamag=
ed? Were cavity inspections, intrusive checks, or residue/chemical tests un=
dertaken? What testing and certification is planned to ensure these critica=
l services are restored to a safe
 and =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D condition?<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><b><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans=
-serif">4. Services =E2=80=93 gas, electricity, and water</span></b><span s=
tyle=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-serif"><o:p>=
</o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">I understand that you are going to test the gas unit and propose a pla=
n to bring it up to new standard, which I appreciate. However, could you al=
so please clarify what is planned for the &nbsp;electricty
