tribution system<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">At present I am unclear how these critical services will be properly t=
ested and reinstated. What testing and certification is planned to ensure t=
hese critical services are restored to a safe
 and =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D condition?<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><b><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans=
-serif">5. Timing and completeness of assessments</span></b><span style=3D"=
font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-serif"><o:p></o:p></=
span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">I am also confused and &nbsp;concerned that a repair plan is already b=
eing discussed before full assessments have been completed and before I hav=
e seen the NZRSC or other formal reports.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">Could you clarify why Tower is progressing toward a repair plan at thi=
s stage rather than awaiting intrusive testing, particularly given the invo=
lvement of corrosive chemicals and deep smoke
 penetration? What testing and certification is planned to ensure these cri=
tical services are restored to a safe and =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D conditio=
n? And what would be the sequencing of those to inform a realistic plan?<o:=
p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">In addition, is it not too risky to wait until after restructuring wor=
ks to determine whether the house is safe and meets code requirements? That=
 approach could prolong reinstatement unnecessarily,
 leaving me at greater disadvantage with accommodation costs and delays tha=
t are outside my control.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><b><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans=
-serif">6. Testing and reporting</span></b><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;f=
ont-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-serif"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">Could you please confirm:<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"1" type=3D"1">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l2 level1 lfo8">What tests or ass=
essments have actually been completed so far?<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"M=
soNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l2 level1 lfo8">Why, given the involvement of s=
pa chemicals, no intrusive testing has been arranged?<o:p></o:p></li><li cl=
ass=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l2 level1 lfo8">When the NZRSC report a=
nd other reports will be made available to me?<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"=
MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l2 level1 lfo8">What testing and certification=
