<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">A number of critical assessments remain outstanding =E2=80=94 includin=
g tests for chemical penetration, the roof structure and cavity, and essent=
ial services such as electricity and water. Until these
 are properly completed and confirmed, the house is uninhabitable.<o:p></o:=
p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">At present, my rental accommodation is being funded under the contents=
 policy ($30,000 limit). However, with reinstatement not yet underway and k=
ey assessments still pending, it is clear this
 allowance will be insufficient. These delays are entirely outside my contr=
ol.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">The Fair Insurance Code requires insurers to act fairly and not disadv=
antage customers through delay. The principle of insurance is to restore th=
e insured to the pre-loss position. To avoid
 being placed at a further disadvantage, I would like to explore the follow=
ing options:<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"1" type=3D"1">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l4 level1 lfo9">Option A: Tower a=
grees I may take the lead in arranging necessary assessments and reinstatem=
ent works, provided all works are to =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D standard, mee=
t current Building Code requirements, and remain within
 the insured sum. Tower would reimburse incurred costs within 15 days of in=
voice on a monthly basis, ensuring timely progress without administrative d=
elay.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l4 level1 lf=
o9">Option B: Alternatively, Tower confirms that it will continue to cover =
my accommodation costs until the house is fully restored and habitable, giv=
en that ongoing delays are not of my making.<o:p></o:p></li></ol>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">Could you please confirm which of these approaches Tower is prepared t=
o adopt, so that I am not unfairly disadvantaged by circumstances outside m=
