<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">Hi Grant,<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">Thank you for your recent email and for the summary of our meeting. I =
appreciate your efforts to move the claim forward.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">There are a few important matters I=E2=80=99d like to clarify to ensur=
e the process remains safe, fair, and aligned with Tower=E2=80=99s responsi=
bilities under the policy.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">First, regarding the items I took with me from the property =E2=80=94 =
including my electric vehicle (EV), laptops, tablets, and mobile phones =E2=
=80=94 these were all exposed to heat, smoke, and corrosive
 chemicals (including nearby spa products that intensified the fire). I rem=
ain concerned about internal damage, particularly to lithium batteries, and=
 the potential for delayed failure or fire.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">It is not appropriate or reasonable for Tower to shift the responsibil=
ity for assessing or managing the risk of these items to me. Ensuring they =
are safe for continued use is a critical safety
 issue =E2=80=94 not just a claims matter. Tower must take responsibility f=
or confirming whether these items are safe, and whether they require restor=
ation or replacement.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">Second, I would appreciate clarification of Asset Restore=E2=80=99s sc=
ope. Is their role limited to cataloguing and removing contents, or will th=
ey also be undertaking removal of fire- or smoke-damaged
 linings (such as jib and other non-structural internal components)? This d=
etail is important for understanding when and how a proper structural asses=
sment of the property will take place.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">Lastly, I would like to request a clear and updated plan for the progr=
ession of the house claim. Could you please provide:<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"1" type=3D"1">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l9 level1 lfo13"><span style=3D"f=
ont-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-serif">A current stat=
us update on the structural assessment and any scoping completed to date;</=
span><o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l9 level1 lf=
o13"><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-=
serif">A proposed timeline for the next phases: removal, scoping, approvals=
, tendering, and repair;</span><o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" styl=
e=3D"mso-list:l9 level1 lfo13"><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&=
quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-serif">Confirmation of the parties responsible fo=
r each stage and how updates will be communicated.</span><o:p></o:p></li></=
ol>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">I look forward to your response addressing the points above.<o:p></o:p=
></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">Kind regards,<br>
Rafaella<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<div class=3D"MsoNormal" align=3D"center" style=3D"text-align:center">
<hr size=3D"1" width=3D"39%" align=3D"center">
</div>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">Let me know if you want to attach the policy wording or include any re=
ferences to specific clauses.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-bottom:12.0pt"><span style=3D"font-s=
ize:10.0pt"><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
<blockquote style=3D"margin-top:5.0pt;margin-bottom:5.0pt">
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">On 22 Jul 2025, at 12:19<span style=3D"font-family:&=
quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">=E2=80=AF</span>PM, Grant Metson &lt;<a href=
=3D"mailto:Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz">Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz</a>&gt; wrote=
:<o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Good afternoon Rafa=
ella,</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I wanted to take th=
e time to thank you very much for meeting with Chris, David and myself at y=
our place this afternoon. It was much appreciated.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I felt that the mee=
ting was very productive and positive as we all discussed the next steps an=
d have agreed on the claim=E2=80=99s progression process moving forward.</s=
pan><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I would like to re-=
confirm the next steps we agreed to in writing, and share with all as below=
:</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><o:p><=
/o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"1" type=3D"1">
<li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-top:0in;margin-bottom:0in;ms=
o-list:l10 level1 lfo14">
<span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Asset Restore to attend site as soon as po=
ssible and complete the process of assessing and cataloging the contents fo=
r the response of the contents claim. After assessment the contents which a=
re categorised as a total loss will
 be removed from site.</span><o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoListParagraph"=
 style=3D"margin-top:0in;margin-bottom:0in;mso-list:l10 level1 lfo14">
<span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Asset Restore to strip out the property of=
 any fire or smoke damaged linings or other non-structural items. This will=
 enable a clear and clean structural assessment to be undertaken, from whic=
h we will produce a scope of works
 for the repairs required.</span><o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoListParagr=
aph" style=3D"margin-top:0in;margin-bottom:0in;mso-list:l10 level1 lfo14">
<span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Once we have a scope of works completed =
=E2=80=93 we will share this with you to approve before we submit to our re=
pair panel for tendering.</span><o:p></o:p></li></ol>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><o:p><=
/o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><o:p><=
/o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Confirming that you=
 have notified us of the access code to be 1106.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">We will keep you up=
dated on the above process and communicate with you as we move through the =
above steps.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><o:p><=
/o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I have spoken with =
both our Motor and our Claims Team Leaders, and they have said that the ite=
ms you have enquired about are very unlikely to be affected by the fire giv=
en their location with respect to the
 proximity of the fire. I do understand that you would like to be 100% cert=
ain that the lithium batteries in these items have not been affected from t=
he fire. The standard process in this situation is that you can undertake a=
ny testing of any of your items
 which you wish to, to obtain test results or a report which your insurer c=
an consider for inclusion in your claims. If the test results prove any dam=
age or loss to these items from the fire =E2=80=93 then your insurer will c=
onsider them within your claim.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><o:p><=
/o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">For contents items =
- please direct your enquiries to<span class=3D"apple-converted-space">&nbs=
p;</span><a href=3D"mailto:claims@tower.co.nz"><span style=3D"color:#467886=
">claims@tower.co.nz</span></a></span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">As you do not yet h=
ave a motor claim with Tower from this event =E2=80=93 you can also send an=
y motor reports to<a href=3D"mailto:claims@tower.co.nz"><span style=3D"colo=
r:#467886">claims@tower.co.nz</span></a><span class=3D"apple-converted-spac=
e">&nbsp;</span>and
 they will respond accordingly.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><o:p><=
/o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Thank you again and=
 I strongly encourage you to call me on the number below with any concerns =
that you have with the process of the claim progression.</span><o:p></o:p><=
/p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">All the best,</span=
><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Grant.<span class=
=3D"apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
